THE body of a man found in Bonnybridge today is thought to be that of missing man Bernard Burall.
Police Scotland issued an appeal for information about Mr Burall on April 1.
Two members of the public found a body in the High Bonnybridge area of the town.
No formal identification has taken place yet, but the family of 49-year-old Mr Burall have been informed by police.
